20rejected%20the%20challenge.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20observed%20that%20the%C2%A0concept%20of%20plurality%20was%20writ%20large%20on%20the%20face%20of%20Article%20324%2C%20Clause%20(2)%20whereof%20clearly%20envisages%20a%20multi-member%20election%20commission%20comprising%20a%20CEC%20and%20one%20or%20more%20ECs.%20If%20a%20multi-member%20election%20commission%20was%20not%20contemplated%2C%20where%20was%20the%20need%20to%20provide%20in%20clause%20(3)%20for%20the%20CEC%20to%20act%20as%20its%20chairman%2C%20the%20Bench%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20no%20room%20for%20doubt%20that%20the%20ECI%20could%20be%20a%20multi-member%20body%2C%20the%20Bench%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20had%20multi-member%20election%20commissions%20in%20operation%20since%201993%2C%20with%20decision-making%20power%20by%20majority%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%202%20last%20year%2C%20a%20Constitution%20Bench%20comprising%20Justices%20K.M.%20Joseph%2C%20Ajay%20Rastogi%2C%20Aniruddha%20Bose%2C%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%20and%20C.T.%20Ravikumar%20had%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fcollegium-for-election-commission-members-supreme-court-takes-away-governments-powers%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0held%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20appointment%20of%20CECs%20and%20ECs%20would%20be%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fexplaining-election-commission-of-india-ruling-supreme-court-checks-executives-power-to-appoint-members-calls-for-balance%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0committee%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0consisting%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20believed%20that%20the%20ECI%20had%20to%20perform%20the%20arduous%20and%20unenviable%20task%20of%20remaining%20aloof%20from%20all%20forms%20of%20subjugation%20by%20and%20interference%20from%20the%20Executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EParliament%20undid%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonths%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%2C%20the%20Parliament%20enacted%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F19721%3Fview_type%3Dbrowse%26sam_handle%3D123456789%2F1362%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Act%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Act%20has%20dropped%20the%20CJI%20from%20the%20selection%20committee%20to%20appoint%20a%20CEC%20and%20ECs.%20The%20selection%20committee%20under%20the%20new%20law%20to%20appoint%20a%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20provides%20the%20Executive%20a%20two-third%20voting%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20also%20provides%20that%20a%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20be%20appointed%20from%20amongst%20persons%20who%20are%20holding%20or%20have%20held%20a%20post%20equivalent%20to%20the%20rank%20of%20secretary%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20and%20who%20are%20persons%20of%20integrity%20with%20knowledge%20of%20and%20experience%20in%20the%20management%20and%20conduct%20of%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20law%2C%20the%20search%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20minister%20of%20law%20and%20justice%20and%20comprising%20two%20other%20members%20not%20below%20the%20rank%20of%20secretary%20to%20the%20government%20of%20India%20shall%20prepare%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20persons%20for%20consideration%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%2C%20for%20appointment%20as%20a%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20a%20panel%20comprising%20the%20Prime%20Minister%3B%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20shall%20recommend%20the%20name%20for%20the%20appointment%20to%20be%20made%20by%20the%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%20also%20provides%20that%20a%20CEC%20and%20ECs%20shall%20hold%20office%20for%20a%20term%20of%20six%20years%20from%20the%20date%20on%20which%20they%20assume%20office%20or%20till%20they%20attain%20the%20age%20of%20sixty-five%20years%2C%20whichever%20is%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20clarifies%20that%20when%20an%20EC%20is%20appointed%20as%20the%20CEC%2C%20his%20term%20of%20office%20shall%20not%20be%20more%20than%20six%20years%20in%20aggregate.%20CECs%20and%20ECs%20shall%20not%20be%20eligible%20for%20re-appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EDifferent%20yardstick%20for%20removal%20of%20CEC%20and%20EC%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20a%20CEC%C2%A0shall%20not%20be%20removed%20from%20his%20office%20except%20in%20like%20manner%20and%20on%20the%20like%20grounds%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20a%20CEC%20shall%20not%20be%20varied%20to%20his%20disadvantage%20after%20his%20appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20removal%20of%20ECs%2C%20the%20Constitution%20provides%20that%20they%20shall%20not%20be%20removed%20from%20office%20except%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20CEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Parliament%20in%20the%202023%20Act%20also%20codified%20the%20same%20notwithstanding%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20observation%20in%20its%20March%202023%20ruling%20that%20it%20was%C2%A0desirable%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20removal%20of%20the%20ECs%20shall%20be%20the%20same%20as%20that%20of%20the%20CEC%2C%20that%20is%2C%20on%20like%20grounds%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20subject%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Erecommendation%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20as%20provided%20under%20the%20second%20proviso%20to%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fexplained-on-arun-goels-resignation-what-is-the-law-on-appointment-and-termination-of-services-of-election-commissioners%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Leaflet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710156729000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Farun-goels-resignation-what-is-the-established-law-on-the-appointment-of-election-commissioners%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20has%20had%20multi-member%20election%20commissions%20in%20operation%20since%201993%2C%20with%20decision-making%20power%20by%20majority%20vote.%20With%20Arun%20Goel's%20resignation%20as%20election%20commissioner%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20one-man%20commission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Farun-goels-resignation-what-is-the-established-law-on-the-appointment-of-election-commissioners%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20'Beyond%20Votes-A%20Slice%20of%20Hope%20Amidst%20Gloom'%3A%20Rajmohan%20Gandhi%20Writes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2015-07%2Fplastic-india-flags_650x400_81437318745.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverything%20does%20NOT%20depend%20solely%20on%20how%20crores%20of%20Indians%20will%20vote%20in%20the%20coming%20election.%20If%20they%20are%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%2C%20just%20two%20individuals%20can%20usher%20in%20a%20gale%20of%20fresh%20air.%20Which%20is%20what%20Justices%20Abhay%20S.%20Oka%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcitizens-have-right-to-criticise-scrapping-of-article-370-supreme-court-5195633%5C%22%3E%20so%20magnificently%20did%20on%20March%207%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20they%20quashed%20proceedings%20that%20had%20been%20launched%20against%20Professor%20Javed%20Ahmad%20Hajam%2C%20who%20hails%20from%20Baramulla%20in%20Kashmir%20but%20was%20teaching%20in%20a%20college%20in%20Kolhapur%2C%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Professor%20Hajam%20was%20hauled%20up%20by%20Maharashtra's%20police%20for%20criticising%20on%20WhatsApp%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20for%20extending%20greetings%20to%20Pakistanis%20on%20their%20Independence%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20question%2C%20the%20justices%20have%20declared%20in%20plain%20language%20that%20criticism%20and%20dissent%20are%20among%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens.%20In%20a%20democracy%2C%20citizens%20are%20perfectly%20entitled%2C%20the%20judges%20have%20laid%20down%2C%20to%20call%20a%20piece%20of%20legislation%20they%20do%20not%20like%2C%20such%20as%20the%20one%20that%20abrogated%20Article%20370%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20black%20Act%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20second%20question%2C%20the%20justices%20pointed%20out%20that%20%26quot%3Bwishing%20people%20of%20Pakistan%20a%20happy%20independence%20day%26quot%3B%20was%20essentially%20%26quot%3Ba%20goodwill%20gesture%26quot%3B.%20Rejecting%20the%20Maharashtra%2