eve%20that%20the%20husband%20stabbed%20his%20wife%20and%20kids.%20An%20anonymous%20call%20alerted%20the%20police.%20This%20incident%20is%20the%20state's%20worst%20mass%20homicides%20since%20the%20Xerox%20murders%20in%201999.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2F5-people-found-dead-in-us-police-suspect-murder-suicide%2Farticleshow%2F108387765.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2F5-people-found-dead-in-us-police-suspect-murder-suicide%2Famp_articleshow%2F108387765.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2F5-people-found-dead-in-us-police-suspect-murder-suicide%2Famp_articleshow%2F108387765.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20BIGGEST%20reunions%20at%20Oscars%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710142607000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108387857%2Cimgsize-51514.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Favengers-peaky-blinders-amazing-spider-man-top-5-biggest-reunions-at-oscars-2024%2Farticleshow%2F108387816.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108387816.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%2096th%20Academy%20Awards%20witnessed%20heartwarming%20reunions%20among%20Hollywood's%20elite%2C%20including%20Chris%20Hemsworth%2C%20Robert%20Downey%20Jr%2C%20Anya%20Taylor-Joy%2C%20Cillian%20Murphy%2C%20Sally%20Field%2C%20Emma%20Stone%2C%20Sam%20Rockwell%2C%20Danny%20DeVito%2C%20and%20Arnold%20Schwarzenegger%2C%20evoking%20nostalgia%20for%20beloved%20characters%20and%20iconic%20moments%20in%20film%20and%20television%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Favengers-peaky-blinders-amazing-spider-man-top-5-biggest-reunions-at-oscars-2024%2Farticleshow%2F108387816.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bonds%20Case%3A%20SC%20Dismisses%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20Plea%20for%20Extension%2C%20Says%20Disclose%20Information%20by%20March%2012%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25132016%2FSupreme-court4.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%20(March%2011)%20dismissed%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20(SBI%E2%80%99s)%20application%20for%20an%20extension%20in%20complying%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20directive%20on%20providing%20details%20related%20to%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20necessary%20information%20is%20already%20available%20with%20the%20bank%2C%20has%20instructed%20the%20SBI%20to%20disclose%20the%20information%20by%20the%20close%20of%20business%20hours%20on%20March%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2015%2C%20the%20top%20court%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20declaring%20it%20unconstitutional%20and%20saying%20that%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20are%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20and%20Article%2019(1)(a).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20ruling%2C%20the%20issuing%20bank%2C%20SBI%2C%20was%20directed%20to%20submit%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20since%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20by%20March%206.%20However%2C%20the%20SBI%20filed%20an%20application%20seeking%20an%20extension%20until%20June%2030%20%E2%80%93%20well%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20to%20be%20held%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20citing%20%E2%80%98complexity%20of%20decoding%20and%20compiling%20data%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20these%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20and%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%2C%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20was%20hearing%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20extension%20plea%20along%20with%20contempt%20petitions%20filed%20by%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20Common%20Cause%2C%20and%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20against%20the%20public%20sector%20bank%20over%20its%20non-disclosure%20of%20vital%20details%20related%20to%20the%20bonds%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-state-bank-of-india-extension-of-time-251814%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%2C%20representing%20the%20SBI%2C%20said%20that%20the%20donor%20details%20and%20redemption%20details%20of%20the%20bonds%20were%20stored%20in%20separate%20information%20silos%20and%20the%20delay%20is%20being%20caused%20due%20to%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20matching%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20this%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20directions%20did%20not%20require%20the%20bank%20to%20conduct%20a%20%E2%80%98matching%20exercise%E2%80%99%20but%20simply%20to%20disclose%20the%20information.%20The%20chief%20justice%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20bank%20had%20all%20the%20necessary%20details%2C%20as%20evidenced%20by%20its%20KYC%20records%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20This%20suggests%20the%20SBI%20does%20not%20have%20to%20disclose%20which%20bonds%20went%20to%20which%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98What%20have%20you%20done%20in%2026%20days%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20questioned%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20the%20progress%20made%20in%20the%2026%20days%20since%20the%20judgment%20was%20issued.%20Salve%20assured%20the%20court%20that%20details%20relating%20to%20the%20progress%20would%20be%20placed%20on%20record%20in%20an%20affidavit.%20%E2%80%9COur%20judgment%20was%20issued%20on%20February%2015.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20March%2011.%20In%20the%20last%2026%20days%2C%20what%20is%20the%20extent%20of%20matching%20done%20by%20you%3F%20The%20affidavit%20is%20silent%20on%20this.%20We%20expect%20a%20degree%20of%20candour%20from%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20the%20details%2C%20I%20am%20not%20saying%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Salve%20told%20the%20court%2C%20before%20reiterating%20that%20the%20difficulty%20was%20caused%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-state-bank-of-india-extension-of-time-251814%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esiloisation%20of%20the%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%20recorded%20by%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20told%20that%20this%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20secret.%20That%20is%20how%20we%20devised%20the%20mechanism.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20now%20create%20any%20havoc%20by%20making%20any%20mistake%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Salve%20argued.%20However%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-state-bank-of-india-extension-of-time-251814%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20question%20of%20any%20mistake.%20You%20have%20the%20KYC.%20You%20are%20the%20number%201%20bank%20in%20the%20country.%20We%20expect%20you%20to%20handle%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%2C%20in%20its%20submissions%20had%20indicated%20that%20all%20purchasing%20details%20were%20kept%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover%20at%20the%20main%20branch.%20Justice%20Khanna%20pointed%20this%20out%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CSimply%20open%20up%20the%20sealed%20cover%2C%20collate%20the%20names%2C%20and%20furnish%20the%20details.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetails%20sought%20from%20the%20SBI%20include%20the%20date%20of%20purchase%2C%20name%20of%20purchaser%20and%20denomination%20of%20each%20electoral%20bond.%20Additionally%2C%20details%20of%20bonds%20cashed%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20date%20of%20such%20encashment%2C%20were%20also%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20in%20its%20final%20order%2C%20said%20%E2%80%9CThe%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20submitted%20that%20the%20donor%20details%20and%20redemption%20details%20are%20available%2C%20albeit%20in%20separate%20silos.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20direction%20issued%20by%20this%20court%20requires%20the%20bank%20to%20disclose%20information%20which%20is%20already%20available%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20regards%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20we%20direct%20them%20to%20compile%20the%20information%20and%20publish%20the%20information%20on%20their%20website%20no%20later%20than%20by%205%20PM%20on%20March%2015%2C%202024%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20order%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20asked%20the%20ECI%20to%20publish%20the%20details%20of%20the%20information%20supplied%20to%20the%20court%20in%20pursuance%20of%20its%20interim%20order%2C%20passed%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20on%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20website.%20In%20that%20order%2C%20the%20court%20had%20asked%20the%20ECI%20for%20details%20of%20the%20funds%20received%20by%20all%20the%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20till%20September%2030%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20new%20March%2012%20deadline%20set%20for%20SBI%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20an%20ECI%20spokesman%20said%20%E2%80%9Cno%20comments%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContempt%20petition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20refusing%20to%20initiate%20contempt%20proceedings%20against%20SBI%2C%20the%20court%20said%20it%20would%20be%20inclined%20to%20proceed%20against%20it%20for%20wilfully%20disobeying%20its%20order%20in%20the%20event%20of%20non-compliance%20with%20the%20latest%20directions%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20shall%20file%20an%20affidavit%20of%20its%20chairperson%20and%20managing%20director%20on%20compliance%20with%20the%20directions%20issued%20above.%20While%20we%20are%20not%20inclined%20to%20exercise%20the%20contempt%20jurisdiction%20at%20this%20time%2C%20we%20place%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20on%20notice%20that%20this%20court%20may%20be%20inclined%20to%20proceed%20against%20it%20for%20wilful%20disobedience%20if%20it%20does%20not%20comply%20with%20the%20timelines%20indicated%20in%20this%20order%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-state-bank-of-india-extension-of-time-251814%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%207%2C%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20representing%20ADR%20and%20Common%20Cause%2C%20had%20requested%20an%20urgent%20hearing%20for%20their%20contempt%20petition%20urging%20the%20court%20to%20list%20it%20with%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20extension%20plea%20scheduled%20to%20be%20heard%20on%20March%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20petition%20alleged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-state-bank-of-india-extension-of-time-251814%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Edeliberate%20defiance%20on%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sought%20contempt%20proceedings%20against%20the%20bank.%20The%20petitioners%20argued%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-state-bank-of-india-extension-of-time-251814%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Ethe%20bank%E2%80%99s%20request%20for%20an%20extension%20is%20%E2%80%98mala%20fide%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20attempt%20to%20thwart%20transparency%20efforts%20ahead%20of%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20pointing%20to%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20sophisticated%20IT%20system%20designed%20to%20manage%20these%20bonds%2C%20the%20petitioners%20argued%20that%20SBI%20was%20capable%20of%20swiftly%20compiling%20and%20disclosing%20the%20information%20it%20already%20possesses.%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20CPI%20(M)%20also%20filed%20a%20contempt%20petition%20against%20the%20SBI%20on%20March%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710142499000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25132016%2FSupreme-court4.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-case-sc-dismisses-sbis-plea-for-extension-says-disclose-information-by-march-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20further%20asked%20the%20ECI%20to%20publish%20these%20details%20on%20their%20website%20no%20later%20than%20March%2015.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A49%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-case-sc-dismisses-sbis-plea-for-extension-says-disclose-information-by-march-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%9814%20Hour%20Work%20Day%2C%20No%20Time%20Off%2C%20Unfair%20Compensation%E2%80%99%3A%20A%20New%20Study%20on%20Gig%20Workers%20Reveals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F11165805%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-11-at-4.57.43-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Almost%2083%25%20app-based%20cab%20drivers%20work%20more%20than%2010%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20while%20working%20hours%20for%20almost%20a%20third%20exceed%2014%20hours%20daily%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgig-workers-suffer-from-lack-of-social-security-regulations-study%2Farticle67936093.ece%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20Indian%20gig%20workers%20has%20revealed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%2C%20conducted%20by%20People%E2%80%99s%20Association%20in%20Grassroots%20Action%20and%20Movements%20and%20the%20Indian%20Federation%20of%20App-based%20Transport%20Workers%2C%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgig-workers-suffer-from-lack-of-social-security-regulations-study%2Farticle67936093.ece%5C%22%3Esocial%20disparities%20are%20replicated%20in%20gig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20only%2016%25%20of%20drivers%20from%20the%20unreserved%20category%20working%20for%20more%20than%2014%20hours%20as%20opposed%20to%2060%25%20of%20drivers%20from%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Tribes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%2C%20involving%205%2C302%20cab%20drivers%20and%205%2C028%20delivery%20persons%20across%20eight%20cities%2C%20also%20revealed%20other%20alarming%20trends.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFinancial%20struggle%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%2043%25%20of%20participants%20earn%20less%20than%20Rs%20500%20a%20day%2C%20or%20Rs%2015%2C000%20a%20month%20after%20deducting%20all%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENearly%2034%25%20app-based%20delivery%20workers%20earn%20less%20than%20Rs%2010%2C000%20a%20month%20while%2078%25%20work%20over%2010%20hours%20a%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHighlighting%20the%20differences%20among%20workers%20from%20different%20castes%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthese%20income%20disparities%20further%20exacerbate%20the%20already%20existing%20social%20inequalities%20and%20perpetuate%20cycles%20of%20poverty%20and%20distress%20within%20these%20communities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20noted%20that%20drivers%20are%20physically%20exhausted%20and%20exposed%20to%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20road%20traffic%20accidents%20due%20to%20long%20working%20hours.%20This%20is%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9810-minute%20delivery%20at%20the%20doorstep%E2%80%99%20policy%20of%20certain%20e-commerce%20platforms.%20The%20report%20said%20that%2086%25%20of%20delivery%20persons%20found%20such%20policies%20%E2%80%9Ccompletely%20unacceptable%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%20also%20found%20that%20nearly%2072%25%20cab%20drivers%20and%2076%25%20delivery%20workers%20are%20unable%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20with%2068%25%20of%20the%20latter%20reporting%20more%20expenses%20than%20their%20income.%20The%20report%20strongly%20advocates%20for%20better%20compensation%20and%20support%20for%20these%20app-based%20workers%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgig-workers-suffer-from-lack-of-social-security-regulations-study%2Farticle67936093.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUnfair%20compensation%2C%20no%20time%20off%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%2080%25%20of%20app-based%20cab%20drivers%20and%2073%25%20of%20delivery%20persons%20expressed%20dissatisfaction%20with%20their%20fares%20and%20rates%20respectively.%20Respondents%20believe%20that%20companies%20deduct%20between%2031-40%25%20of%20the%20commission%20rate%20per%20ride%2C%20contrary%20to%20officially%20claimed%20figures%20of%2020%25%2C%20with%2068%25%20finding%20these%20deductions%20arbitrary%2C%20unexplained%2C%20and%20unfair.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20the%20low%20pay%2C%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20workers%20struggled%20to%20take%20time%20off%20with%2041%25%20of%20drivers%20and%2048%25%20of%20delivery%20persons%20being%20unable%20to%20take%20a%20single%20day%20off%20in%20a%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20highlighte